  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_5' aria-label=\" Lal Mohd. & Anr. versus State of U.P. & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('5','2025','2025_5_741_763','2025INSC811'); ><font size='4'> <strong>LAL MOHD. & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF U.P. & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 741</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 811</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004272025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the prosecution of the appellants under the UP Gangsters Act satisfies the statutory thresholds prescribed under the Act, when it is based entirely on a single FIR, in which the appellants were already arrested and released on bail, and where no new act or omission of the First FIR i.e., 11.10.2022, and the preparation of the gang chart on 29.04.2023. Headnotes&dagger; Uttar Pradesh Gangsters &amp; Anti-Social Activities (Prevention) Act, 1986 &ndash; s.2(b), (c) &ndash; First FIR was registered against the appellants and others on 11.10.2022 for<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2593/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('5','2025','2025_5_741_763','2025INSC811','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' cla